name: dataproc
title: Google Cloud Dataproc API
description: Manages Hadoop-based clusters and jobs on Google Cloud Platform.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

schemas.name: ClusterMetrics
schemas.desc: Contains cluster daemon metrics, such as HDFS and YARN stats.

fields.name: hdfsMetrics
fields.desc: The HDFS metrics.

fields.name: yarnMetrics
fields.desc: The YARN metrics.

schemas.name: GceClusterConfiguration
schemas.desc: Common configuration settings for resources of Google Compute Engine cluster instances, applicable to all instances in the cluster.

fields.name: metadata
fields.desc: The Google Compute Engine metadata entries to add to all instances.

fields.name: internalIpOnly
fields.desc: If true, all instances in the cluser will only have internal IP addresses. By default, clusters are not restricted to internal IP addresses, and will have ephemeral external IP addresses assigned to each instance. This restriction can only be enabled for subnetwork enabled networks, and all off-cluster dependencies must be configured to be accessible without external IP addresses.

fields.name: serviceAccountScopes
fields.desc: The service account scopes included in Google Compute Engine instances. Must include devstorage.full_control to enable the Google Cloud Storage connector. Example "auth.googleapis.com/compute" and "auth.googleapis.com/devstorage.full_control".

fields.name: tags
fields.desc: The Google Compute Engine tags to add to all instances.

fields.name: serviceAccount
fields.desc:
Optional The service account of the instances. Defaults to the default Google Compute Engine service account. Custom service accounts need permissions equivalent to the folloing IAM roles:
roles/logging.logWriter
roles/storage.objectAdmin(see https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/access/service-accounts#custom_service_accounts for more information). Example: [account_id]@[project_id].iam.gserviceaccount.com

fields.name: subnetworkUri
fields.desc: The Google Compute Engine subnetwork to be used for machine communications. Cannot be specified with network_uri. Example: compute.googleapis.com/projects/[project_id]/regions/us-east1/sub0.

fields.name: networkUri
fields.desc: The Google Compute Engine network to be used for machine communications. Cannot be specified with subnetwork_uri. If neither network_uri nor subnetwork_uri is specified, the "default" network of the project is used, if it exists. Cannot be a "Custom Subnet Network" (see https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/subnetworks for more information). Example: compute.googleapis.com/projects/[project_id]/regions/global/default.

fields.name: zoneUri
fields.desc: Required The zone where the Google Compute Engine cluster will be located. Example: "compute.googleapis.com/projects/project_id /zones/us-east1-a".

schemas.name: JobStatus
schemas.desc: Cloud Dataproc job status.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time when the server started the job.

fields.name: insertTime
fields.desc: The time of the job request.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: Required A state message specifying the overall job state.

enum.name: PENDING
enum.desc: The job is pending; it has been submitted, but is not yet running.

enum.name: SETUP_DONE
enum.desc: Job has been received by the service and completed initial setup; it will shortly be submitted to the cluster.

enum.name: RUNNING
enum.desc: The job is running on the cluster.

enum.name: CANCEL_PENDING
enum.desc: A CancelJob request has been received, but is pending.

enum.name: CANCEL_STARTED
enum.desc: Transient in-flight resources have been canceled, and the request to cancel the running job has been issued to the cluster.

enum.name: ERROR
enum.desc: The job has completed, but encountered an error.

enum.name: ATTEMPT_FAILURE
enum.desc: Job attempt has failed. The detail field contains failure details for this attempt.Applies to restartable jobs only.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: Optional Job state details, such as an error description if the state is ERROR.

fields.name: stateStartTime
fields.desc: Output-only The time when this state was entered.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time when the job completed.

schemas.name: HiveJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running Hive queries on YARN.

fields.name: continueOnFailure
fields.desc: Optional Whether to continue executing queries if a query fails. The default value is false. Setting to true can be useful when executing independent parallel queries.

fields.name: queryFileUri
fields.desc: The HCFS URI of the script that contains Hive queries.

fields.name: queryList
fields.desc: A list of queries.

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of jar files to add to the CLASSPATH of the Hive server and Hadoop MapReduce (MR) tasks. Can contain Hive SerDes and UDFs.

fields.name: scriptVariables
fields.desc: Optional Mapping of query variable names to values (equivalent to the Hive command: 'SET name="value";').

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names and values, used to configure Hive. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten. Can include properties set in /etc/hadoop/conf/*-site.xml, /etc/hive/conf/hive-site.xml, and classes in user code.

schemas.name: SparkSqlJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running Spark SQL queries.

fields.name: queryFileUri
fields.desc: The HCFS URI of the script that contains SQL queries.

fields.name: queryList
fields.desc: A list of queries.

fields.name: scriptVariables
fields.desc: Optional Mapping of query variable names to values (equivalent to the Spark SQL command: SET name="value";).

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of jar files to be added to the Spark CLASSPATH.

fields.name: loggingConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The runtime log configuration for job execution.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names to values, used to configure Spark SQL's SparkConf. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten.

schemas.name: OperationMetadata
schemas.desc: Metadata describing the operation.

fields.name: operationType
fields.desc: Output-only The operation type.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Output-only Short description of operation.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: A message containing the operation state.

enum.name: DONE
enum.desc: The operation is done, either cancelled or completed.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: A message containing any operation metadata details.

fields.name: innerState
fields.desc: A message containing the detailed operation state.

fields.name: statusHistory
fields.desc: Output-only Previous operation status.

fields.name: insertTime
fields.desc: The time that the operation was requested.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: Output-only Current operation status.

fields.name: clusterUuid
fields.desc: Cluster UUId for the operation.

fields.name: clusterName
fields.desc: Name of the cluster for the operation.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time that the operation completed.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time that the operation was started by the server.

fields.name: warnings
fields.desc: Output-only Errors encountered during operation execution.

schemas.name: ManagedGroupConfiguration
schemas.desc: Specifies the resources used to actively manage an instance group.

fields.name: instanceGroupManagerName
fields.desc: Output-only The name of Instance Group Manager managing this group.

fields.name: instanceTemplateName
fields.desc: Output-only The name of Instance Template used for Managed Instance Group.

schemas.name: GceConfiguration
schemas.desc: Deprecated Common configuration settings for resources of Google Compute Engine cluster instances, applicable to all instances in the cluster.

fields.name: machineTypeUri
fields.desc: Deprecated The Google Compute Engine machine type used for cluster instances. Example: "compute.googleapis.com/projects/project_id /zones/us-east1-a/machineTypes/n1-standard-2".

fields.name: networkUri
fields.desc: Deprecated The Google Compute Engine network to be used for machine communications. Inbound SSH connections are necessary to complete cluster configuration. Example "compute.googleapis.com/projects/project_id /zones/us-east1-a/default".

fields.name: serviceAccountScopes
fields.desc: Deprecated The service account scopes included in Google Compute Engine instances. Must include devstorage.full_control to enable the Google Cloud Storage connector. Example "auth.googleapis.com/compute" and "auth.googleapis.com/devstorage.full_control".

fields.name: zoneUri
fields.desc: Deprecated The zone where the Google Compute Engine cluster will be located. Example: "compute.googleapis.com/projects/project_id /zones/us-east1-a".

fields.name: imageUri

schemas.name: PySparkJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running PySpark applications on YARN.

fields.name: mainPythonFileUri
fields.desc: Required The Hadoop Compatible Filesystem (HCFS) URI of the main Python file to use as the driver. Must be a .py file.

fields.name: archiveUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of archives to be extracted in the working directory of .jar, .tar, .tar.gz, .tgz, and .zip.

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of jar files to add to the CLASSPATHs of the Python driver and tasks.

fields.name: loggingConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The runtime log configuration for job execution.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names to values, used to configure PySpark. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten. Can include properties set in /etc/spark/conf/spark-defaults.conf and classes in user code.

fields.name: args
fields.desc: Optional The arguments to pass to the driver. Do not include arguments, such as --conf, that can be set as job properties, since a collision may occur that causes an incorrect job submission.

fields.name: fileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of files to be copied to the working directory of Python drivers and distributed tasks. Useful for naively parallel tasks.

fields.name: pythonFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS file URIs of Python files to pass to the PySpark framework. Supported file types: .py, .egg, and .zip.

schemas.name: Operation
schemas.desc: An asynchronous operation in a project that runs over a given cluster. Used to track the progress of a user request that is running asynchronously. Examples include creating a cluster, updating a cluster, and deleting a cluster.

fields.name: done
fields.desc: Indicates if the operation is done. If true, the operation is complete and the result is available. If false, the operation is still in progress.

fields.name: response
fields.desc: The operation response. If the called method returns no data on success, the response is google.protobuf.Empty. If the called method is Get,Create or Update, the response is the resource. For all other methods, the response type is a concatenation of the method name and "Response". For example, if the called method is TakeSnapshot(), the response type is TakeSnapshotResponse.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the operation resource, in the format projects/project_id/operations/operation_id

fields.name: error
fields.desc: The error result of the operation in case of failure.

fields.name: metadata
fields.desc: Service-specific metadata associated with the operation.

schemas.name: NodeInitializationAction
schemas.desc: Specifies an executable to run on a fully configured node and a timeout period for executable completion.

fields.name: executableFile
fields.desc: Required Google Cloud Storage URI of executable file.

fields.name: executionTimeout
fields.desc: Optional Amount of time executable has to complete. Default is 10 minutes. Cluster creation fails with an explanatory error message (the name of the executable that caused the error and the exceeded timeout period) if the executable is not completed at end of the timeout period.

schemas.name: CancelJobRequest
schemas.desc: A request to cancel a job.

schemas.name: LoggingConfiguration
schemas.desc: The runtime logging configuration of the job.

fields.name: driverLogLevels
fields.desc: The per-package log levels for the driver. This may include 'root' package name to configure rootLogger. Examples:  com.google = FATAL, root = INFO, org.apache = DEBUG

schemas.name: InstanceGroupConfiguration
schemas.desc: The configuration settings for Google Compute Engine resources in an instance group, such as a master or worker group.

fields.name: isPreemptible
fields.desc: Specifies that this instance group contains Preemptible Instances.

fields.name: managedGroupConfiguration
fields.desc: Output-only The configuration for Google Compute Engine Instance Group Manager that manages this group. This is only used for preemptible instance groups.

fields.name: instanceNames
fields.desc: The list of instance names. Dataproc derives the names from cluster_name, num_instances, and the instance group if not set by user (recommended practice is to let Dataproc derive the name).

fields.name: accelerators
fields.desc: Optional The Google Compute Engine accelerator configuration for these instances.

fields.name: numInstances
fields.desc: The number of VM instances in the instance group. For master instance groups, must be set to 1.

fields.name: diskConfiguration
fields.desc: Disk option configuration settings.

fields.name: machineTypeUri
fields.desc: The Google Compute Engine machine type used for cluster instances. Example: "compute.googleapis.com/projects/project_id /zones/us-east1-a/machineTypes/n1-standard-2".

fields.name: imageUri
fields.desc: Output-only The Google Compute Engine image resource used for cluster instances. Inferred from SoftwareConfiguration.image_version. Example: "compute.googleapis.com/projects/debian-cloud /global/images/backports-debian-7-wheezy-v20140904".

schemas.name: OperationStatus
schemas.desc: The status of the operation.

fields.name: stateStartTime
fields.desc: The time this state was entered.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: A message containing the operation state.

enum.name: DONE
enum.desc: The operation is done; either cancelled or completed.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: A message containing any operation metadata details.

fields.name: innerState
fields.desc: A message containing the detailed operation state.

schemas.name: PigJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running Pig queries on YARN.

fields.name: loggingConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The runtime log configuration for job execution.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names to values, used to configure Pig. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten. Can include properties set in /etc/hadoop/conf/*-site.xml, /etc/pig/conf/pig.properties, and classes in user code.

fields.name: continueOnFailure
fields.desc: Optional Whether to continue executing queries if a query fails. The default value is false. Setting to true can be useful when executing independent parallel queries.

fields.name: queryFileUri
fields.desc: The HCFS URI of the script that contains the Pig queries.

fields.name: queryList
fields.desc: A list of queries.

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of jar files to add to the CLASSPATH of the Pig Client and Hadoop MapReduce (MR) tasks. Can contain Pig UDFs.

fields.name: scriptVariables
fields.desc: Optional Mapping of query variable names to values (equivalent to the Pig command: "name=value").

schemas.name: JobScheduling
schemas.desc: Job scheduling options.Beta Feature: These options are available for testing purposes only. They may be changed before final release.

fields.name: maxFailuresPerHour
fields.desc: Optional Maximum number of times per hour a driver may be restarted as a result of driver terminating with non-zero code before job is reported failed.A job may be reported as thrashing if driver exits with non-zero code 4 times within 10 minute window.Maximum value is 10.

schemas.name: ListJobsResponse
schemas.desc: A response to a request to list jobs in a project.

fields.name: jobs
fields.desc: Output-only Jobs list.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Optional This token is included in the response if there are more results to fetch. To fetch additional results, provide this value as the page_token in a subsequent ListJobsRequest.

schemas.name: Cluster
schemas.desc: Describes the identifying information, configuration, and status of a cluster of Google Compute Engine instances.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: Optional The labels to associate with this cluster.Label keys must be between 1 and 63 characters long, and must conform to the following PCRE regular expression: \p{Ll}\p{Lo}{0,62}Label values must be between 1 and 63 characters long, and must conform to the following PCRE regular expression: \p{Ll}\p{Lo}\p{N}_-{0,63}No more than 64 labels can be associated with a given cluster.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: Output-only Cluster status.

fields.name: statusHistory
fields.desc: Output-only Previous cluster statuses.

fields.name: clusterName
fields.desc: Required The cluster name. Cluster names within a project must be unique. Names from deleted clusters can be reused.

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: Required The Google Cloud Platform project ID that the cluster belongs to.

fields.name: configuration
fields.desc: Required The cluster configuration. It may differ from a user's initial configuration due to Cloud Dataproc setting of default values and updating clusters.

fields.name: createTime
fields.desc: Output-only The timestamp of cluster creation.

fields.name: metrics
fields.desc: Contains cluster daemon metrics such as HDFS and YARN stats.

fields.name: clusterUuid
fields.desc: Output-only A cluster UUID (Unique Universal Identifier). Cloud Dataproc generates this value when it creates the cluster.

schemas.name: HadoopJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running Hadoop MapReduce jobs on YARN.

fields.name: args
fields.desc: Optional The arguments to pass to the driver. Do not include arguments, such as -libjars or -Dfoo=bar, that can be set as job properties, since a collision may occur that causes an incorrect job submission.

fields.name: fileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of files to be copied to the working directory of Hadoop drivers and distributed tasks. Useful for naively parallel tasks.

fields.name: mainClass
fields.desc: The name of the driver's main class. The jar file containing the class must be in the default CLASSPATH or specified in jar_file_uris.

fields.name: archiveUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of archives to be extracted in the working directory of Hadoop drivers and tasks. Supported file types: .jar, .tar, .tar.gz, .tgz, or .zip.

fields.name: mainJarFileUri
fields.desc: The Hadoop Compatible Filesystem (HCFS) URI of the jar file containing the main class. Examples:  gs://foo-bucket/analytics-binaries/extract-useful-metrics-mr.jar  hdfs:/tmp/test-samples/custom-wordcount.jar  file:///home/usr/lib/hadoop-mapreduce/hadoop-mapreduce-examples.jar

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional Jar file URIs to add to the CLASSPATHs of the Hadoop driver and tasks.

fields.name: loggingConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The runtime log configuration for job execution.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names to values, used to configure Hadoop. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten. Can include properties set in /etc/hadoop/conf/*-site and classes in user code.

schemas.name: Empty
SoftwareConfiguration
schemas.desc: Specifies the selection and configuration of software inside the cluster.

fields.name: imageVersion
fields.desc: Optional The version of software inside the cluster. It must match the regular expression 0-9+.0-9+. If unspecified it will default to latest version.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional The properties to set on daemon configuration files.Property keys are specified in "prefix:property" format, such as "core:fs.defaultFS". The following are supported prefixes and their mappings:  core - core-site.xml  hdfs - hdfs-site.xml  mapred - mapred-site.xml  yarn - yarn-site.xml  hive - hive-site.xml  pig - pig.properties  spark - spark-defaults.conf

schemas.name: SparkJob
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job for running Spark applications on YARN.

fields.name: loggingConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The runtime log configuration for job execution.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: Optional A mapping of property names to values, used to configure Spark. Properties that conflict with values set by the Cloud Dataproc API may be overwritten. Can include properties set in /etc/spark/conf/spark-defaults.conf and classes in user code.

fields.name: args
fields.desc: Optional The arguments to pass to the driver. Do not include arguments, such as --conf, that can be set as job properties, since a collision may occur that causes an incorrect job submission.

fields.name: fileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of files to be copied to the working directory of Spark drivers and distributed tasks. Useful for naively parallel tasks.

fields.name: mainClass
fields.desc: The name of the driver's main class. The jar file that contains the class must be in the default CLASSPATH or specified in jar_file_uris.

fields.name: archiveUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of archives to be extracted in the working directory of Spark drivers and tasks. Supported file types: .jar, .tar, .tar.gz, .tgz, and .zip.

fields.name: mainJarFileUri
fields.desc: The Hadoop Compatible Filesystem (HCFS) URI of the jar file that contains the main class.

fields.name: jarFileUris
fields.desc: Optional HCFS URIs of jar files to add to the CLASSPATHs of the Spark driver and tasks.

schemas.name: DiskConfiguration
schemas.desc: Specifies the configuration of disk options for a group of VM instances.

fields.name: numLocalSsds
fields.desc: Optional Number of attached SSDs, from 0 to 4 (default is 0). If SSDs are not attached, the boot disk is used to store runtime logs, and HDFS data. If one or more SSDs are attached, this runtime bulk data is spread across them, and the boot disk contains only basic configuration and installed binaries.

fields.name: bootDiskSizeGb
fields.desc: Optional Size in GB of the boot disk (default is 500GB).

schemas.name: DiagnoseClusterResults
schemas.desc: The location of diagnostic output.

fields.name: outputUri
fields.desc: Output-only The Google Cloud Storage URI of the diagnostic output. The output report is a plain text file with a summary of collected diagnostics.

schemas.name: ListJobsRequest
schemas.desc: A request to list jobs in a project.

fields.name: pageSize
fields.desc: Optional The number of results to return in each response.

fields.name: filter
fields.desc: Optional A filter constraining which jobs to list. Valid filters contain job state and label terms such as: labels.key1 = val1 AND (labels.k2 = val2 OR labels.k3 = val3)

fields.name: jobStateMatcher
fields.desc: Optional Specifies enumerated categories of jobs to list.

enum.name: ALL
enum.desc: Match all jobs, regardless of state.

enum.name: ACTIVE
enum.desc: Only match jobs in non-terminal states: PENDING, RUNNING, CANCEL_PENDING

enum.name: NON_ACTIVE
enum.desc: Only match jobs in terminal states: CANCELLED, DONE, ERROR

fields.name: pageToken
fields.desc: Optional The page token, returned by a previous call, to request the next page of results.

fields.name: clusterName
fields.desc: Optional If set, the returned jobs list includes only jobs that were submitted to the named cluster.

schemas.name: CancelOperationRequest
schemas.desc: The request message for Operations.CancelOperation.

schemas.name: SubmitJobRequest
schemas.desc: A job submission request.

fields.name: job
fields.desc: Required The job resource.

schemas.name: ClusterStatus
schemas.desc: The status of a cluster and its instances.

fields.name: stateStartTime
fields.desc: Time when this state was entered.

fields.name: detail
fields.desc: Optional details of cluster's state.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: The cluster's state.

enum.name: CREATING
enum.desc: The cluster is being created and set up. It is not ready for use.

enum.name: RUNNING
enum.desc: The cluster is currently running and healthy. It is ready for use.

enum.name: ERROR
enum.desc: The cluster encountered an error. It is not ready for use.

enum.name: DELETING
enum.desc: The cluster is being deleted. It cannot be used.

enum.name: UPDATING
enum.desc: The cluster is being updated. It continues to accept and process jobs.

schemas.name: Job
schemas.desc: A Cloud Dataproc job resource.

fields.name: sparkJob
fields.desc: Job is a Spark job.

fields.name: reference
fields.desc: Optional The fully-qualified reference to the job, which can be used to obtain the equivalent REST path of the job resource. If this property is not specified when a job is created, the server generates a job_id.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: Output-only The job status. Additional application-specific status information may be contained in the type_job and yarn_applications fields.

fields.name: submittedBy
fields.desc: Output-only The email address of the user submitting the job. For jobs submitted on the cluster, the address is username@hostname.

fields.name: hiveJob
fields.desc: Job is a Hive job.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: Optional The labels to associate with this job.Label keys must be between 1 and 63 characters long, and must conform to the following regular expression: \p{Ll}\p{Lo}{0,62}Label values must be between 1 and 63 characters long, and must conform to the following regular expression: \p{Ll}\p{Lo}\p{N}_-{0,63}No more than 64 labels can be associated with a given job.

fields.name: hadoopJob
fields.desc: Job is a Hadoop job.

fields.name: driverControlFilesUri
fields.desc: Output-only If present, the location of miscellaneous control files which may be used as part of job setup and handling. If not present, control files may be placed in the same location as driver_output_uri.

fields.name: pigJob
fields.desc: Job is a Pig job.

fields.name: driverOutputUri
fields.desc: Output-only A URI pointing to the location of the mixed stdout/stderr of the job's driver program—for example, gs://sysbucket123/foo-cluster/jobid-123/driver/output.

fields.name: sparkSqlJob
fields.desc: Job is a SparkSql job.

fields.name: scheduling
fields.desc: Optional Job scheduling configuration.

fields.name: driverOutputResourceUri
fields.desc: Output-only A URI pointing to the location of the stdout of the job's driver program.

fields.name: yarnApplications
fields.desc: Output-only The collection of Yarn applications spun up by this job.

fields.name: interactive
fields.desc: Optional If set to true, then the driver's stdin will be kept open and driver_input_uri will be set to provide a path at which additional input can be sent to the driver.

fields.name: placement
fields.desc: Required Job information, including how, when, and where to run the job.

fields.name: statusHistory
fields.desc: Output-only The previous job status.

fields.name: pysparkJob
fields.desc: Job is a Pyspark job.

fields.name: driverInputResourceUri
fields.desc: Output-only A URI pointing to the location of the stdin of the job's driver program, only set if the job is interactive.

schemas.name: YarnApplication
schemas.desc: A YARN application created by a job. Application information is a subset of org.apache.hadoop.yarn.proto.YarnProtos.ApplicationReportProto.

fields.name: trackingUrl
fields.desc: Optional The HTTP URL of the ApplicationMaster, HistoryServer, or TimelineServer that provides application-specific information. The URL uses the internal hostname, and requires a proxy server for resolution and, possibly, access.

fields.name: progress
fields.desc: Required The numerical progress of the application, from 1 to 100.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: Required The application state.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Required The application name.

schemas.name: ClusterConfiguration
schemas.desc: The cluster configuration.

fields.name: softwareConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The configuration settings for software inside the cluster.

fields.name: gceClusterConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The shared Google Compute Engine configuration settings for all instances in a cluster.

fields.name: numWorkers
fields.desc: Deprecated The number of worker nodes in the cluster.

fields.name: masterConfiguration
fields.desc: Optional The Google Compute Engine configuration settings for the master instance in a cluster.

fields.name: workerConfiguration

schemas.name: Status
schemas.desc:
The Status type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is used by gRPC (https://github.com/grpc). The error model is designed to be:
Simple to use and understand for most users
Flexible enough to meet unexpected needsOverviewThe Status message contains three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details. The error code should be an enum value of google.rpc.Code, but it may accept additional error codes if needed. The error message should be a developer-facing English message that helps developers understand and resolve the error. If a localized user-facing error message is needed, put the localized message in the error details or localize it in the client. The optional error details may contain arbitrary information about the error. There is a predefined set of error detail types in the package google.rpc which can be used for common error conditions.Language mappingThe Status message is the logical representation of the error model, but it is not necessarily the actual wire format. When the Status message is exposed in different client libraries and different wire protocols, it can be mapped differently. For example, it will likely be mapped to some exceptions in Java, but more likely mapped to some error codes in C.Other usesThe error model and the Status message can be used in a variety of environments, either with or without APIs, to provide a consistent developer experience across different environments.Example uses of this error model include:
Partial errors. If a service needs to return partial errors to the client, it may embed the Status in the normal response to indicate the partial errors.
Workflow errors. A typical workflow has multiple steps. Each step may have a Status message for error reporting purpose.
Batch operations. If a client uses batch request and batch response, the Status message should be used directly inside batch response, one for each error sub-response.
Asynchronous operations. If an API call embeds asynchronous operation results in its response, the status of those operations should be represented directly using the Status message.
Logging. If some API errors are stored in logs, the message Status could be used directly after any stripping needed for security/privacy reasons.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: A list of messages that carry the error details. There will be a common set of message types for APIs to use.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: The status code, which should be an enum value of google.rpc.Code.

fields.name: message
fields.desc: A developer-facing error message, which should be in English. Any user-facing error message should be localized and sent in the google.rpc.Status.details field, or localized by the client.

methods.name: cancel
methods.desc: Starts asynchronous cancellation on a long-running operation. The server makes a best effort to cancel the operation, but success is not guaranteed. If the server doesn't support this method, it returns google.rpc.Code.UNIMPLEMENTED. Clients may use Operations.GetOperation or other methods to check whether the cancellation succeeded or the operation completed despite cancellation.

pathParams.name: name
pathParams.desc: The name of the operation resource to be cancelled.

methods.name: delete
methods.desc: Deletes a long-running operation. It indicates the client is no longer interested in the operation result. It does not cancel the operation.

pathParams.name: name

methods.name: get
methods.desc: Gets the latest state of a long-running operation. Clients may use this method to poll the operation result at intervals as recommended by the API service.

methods.name: list
methods.desc: Lists operations that match the specified filter in the request. If the server doesn't support this method, it returns google.rpc.Code.UNIMPLEMENTED.

pathParams.name: name
pathParams.desc: The operation collection name.

optinalQueryParams.name: filter
optinalQueryParams.desc: Required A JSON object that contains filters for the list operation, in the format {"key1":"value1","key2":"value2", ..., }. Possible keys include project_id, cluster_name, and operation_state_matcher.If project_id is set, requests the list of operations that belong to the specified Google Cloud Platform project ID. This key is required.If cluster_name is set, requests the list of operations that were submitted to the specified cluster name. This key is optional.If operation_state_matcher is set, requests the list of operations that match one of the following status options: ALL, ACTIVE, or NON_ACTIVE.
